Aloha President Kouchi, Speaker Nakamura and Members of the Legislature:
Transmitted herewith are proposed changes to the FB 2025-27 Executive Budget for
the operating and capital improvement program (CIP) budget requests, as applicable,
for the Departments of Education and Transportation.
Your favorable consideration would be appreciated for the following budget requests to
amend the FB 2025-27 Executive Budget.
1 . Adjustments to the Operating Budget Request:
The following additional budget requests are being proposed to update amounts
requested in the operating budget:
Department of Education
School Support - Food Services (EDN 400/MD)
Add $20,000,000 in general funds for FY 26 for the Food Services Program shortfall
due to increased costs to provide students meals. The projected deficit can be
attributed to a multitu_de of factors, including increased operating costs, rising food
prices, and steady school meal prices charged to students.
The Honorable Ronald D. Kouchi
The Honorable Nadine K. Nakamura
March 28, 2025
Page Two of Two
Department of Transportation
Highways Administration (TRN 595/DB)
Add $2,400,000 in special funds for FY 26 and $2,800,000 in special funds for FY 27
to maintain and expand the Photo Red Light Imaging Detector System, including
seeking additional locations to expand to the neighbor islands, and provide staffing
for the county Office of the Prosecuting Attorneys and the four county police
departments.

Section 2:
2. Adjustments to the CIP Request:
The following additional budget request is being proposed to update amounts
requested in the CIP budget:
Department of Transportation
Airports Administration (TRN 195)
Add $1,373,000 in special funds for FY 26 and FY 27 to Airports Division Capital
Improvement Program Project Staff Costs, Statewide, Item C-11, for additional
plans, design, and construction. House Bill No. 300 currently includes $6,127,000 in
special funds and $200,000 in other funds for FY 26 and FY 27. An additional
$1,373,000 in special funds for both fiscal years are to fund wages and fringe for
nine new project-funded staff positions to create a new airfield section to implement
military airfield reconstruction.
Mahalo,

